Package queuewithstacks

Class PseudoQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • queuewithstacks.PseudoQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Queue
    public class PseudoQueue
extends java.lang.Object
implements Queue
    Stack implementation of a Queue data structure. Utilizes two mutually exclusive stacks; 1. Stack enQueue: it's a backwards queue in that the bottom of the stack represents the front of the queue. 2. Stack deQueue: it's a forwards queue in that the top, where you pop, represents the front of the queue. Mutually exclusive here means that only one of the two can have nodes at a time. What drives which stack has the nodes at any given moment? It depends on the last push, or peek/pop action. If the last action was push, then enQueue has the nodes. If the last action was peek or pop, then the deQueue has the nodes.
